    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="752"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 212.11G/10.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Refers to the embassy’s No. 86 of June 8, and states that the foreign office asks
                    when the proofs against Heliodoro Garcia may be presented.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
